issue.title: Getting Yak list failed
issue.body:
First of all, thanks for the comprehensive package and nice documentation. I was trying to run your example code, but after this line: 

> > > user = User(exeter, "21C6CA60E3AA43C4B8C18B943394E111")
> > > , I get the following error:
> > > raise ParsingResponseError("Getting Yak list failed", raw_data)
> > > ParsingResponseError: Getting Yak list failed
> > > Response:
> > > Do you know what causes that? I tried different UserIDs too. But, it didn't help.

Thanks.
